parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Wiring Harness Causing Speaker Failure and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective wiring harness can cause the speakers to fail, leading to a fire hazard, which can result in damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.

symptoms: The rotors need to be replaced frequently (every 10

the vehicle shakes violently while braking
the steering wheel vibrates out of control while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty Bose speaker system can cause a fire, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear speakers produce unusual noises
including hum
hissing
squeal
and popping sounds

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control Malfunction Causing Unintended Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to a loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle becomes stuck in the open position
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and unexpectedly
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries to the driver and occupants, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without being involved in an accident
the airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag module malfunctioning
sudden and unexpected deployment of the airbag.
